BBC.Six.Nations.Rugby.2016.02.06.France.v.Italy.1080i.h264-NX

Gabby Logan is joined by Thomas Castaignede and Keith Wood for live coverage of the opening game of the 2016 Six Nations Championship as France host Italy. France have a proud history in the tournament but have not lifted the trophy since 2010, something new head coach Guy Noves will be aiming to rectify. Following a disappointing performance at the World Cup and the retirement of players such as captain Thierry Dusautoir, a new-look team takes to the field for Les Bleus. Italy, meanwhile, hope to catch their hosts cold and land a repeat of the 23-18 opening game win over France in Rome in 2013. Commentary is by Eddie Butler, Jonathan Davies and Carlo Del Fava.
